odot$. Second, a characteristic feature at $10 \\mu \\rm{m}$ due to the\namorphous silicate band appears as a dip at $1Z_{\\odot}$, but changes to a bump\nat $Z \\lesssim 0.1 Z_{\\odot}$. Using these spectral signatures, we can search\nmassive accreting protostars in nearby low-metallicity environments with\nup-coming observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Oct 2017 03:31:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
